# Slidev Slide Creation & Editing Guide

## Quick Reference for Common Slide Patterns

Follow [slide-styling-guidelines.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/slide-creation/slide-styling-guidelines.mdc) to make sure slides do not overflow the page and look nice. 

### Layout Decision Matrix
- Cover → `layout: cover`
- Section/Agenda → `layout: section`
- Text list → `layout: default` + `max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-2`
- Comparison → grid `grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 items-start`
- Image focus → `layout: center` or two‑column text+image
- Code → `layout: default`, ≤ 16 visible lines; use highlights
- Diagram → Mermaid `graph LR`, ≤ 7 nodes
- Quote → `layout: quote`

### Density Guardrails
- Bullets: max 4–5 per slide, 5–7 words each
- Columns: ≤ 4 bullets per column
- Code: ≤ 16 lines; split or stage via highlights
- Diagram: ≤ 7 nodes; short labels
- If exceeded → split slide or reveal groups with `<v-clicks>`

### Responsive Helpers
- Spacing: `p-2 sm:p-3 md:p-4`, `space-y-2`
- Width: `max-w-3xl mx-auto`
- Typography: `text-base md:text-lg leading-tight`

